Cell_bank: European Collection of Authenticated Cell Cultures (Porton Down, UK)
OBS: SH-SY5Y human neuroblastoma cells (ECACC No. 94030304). Once the cells were 80% confluent, they were used forexperimental purpose; immediately, the medium was replacedwith fresh Advanced DMEM/F12 containing GlutaMAXTM-I supple-mented with 3% FBS. The MTT reagent (15 uL) was then added per well, and the cells were incubated for an additional 4 h. The formazan crystalswere solubilized by adding 100 L/well of solubilizer (10% sodiumdodecyl sulphate (SDS), 3.2 mM HCl) and the plates were placedovernight at 37◦C. The absorbance (A570) of the resulting coloredsolution was measured with a microplate reader (iMark, Bio-Rad).

Ab (1–40) was produced at the peptide synthesis facility of the University of W€urzburg with a
Zinsser simultaneous multiple peptide synthesiser using a Fmoc-protection and DIC=HOBt activating
chemistry as described previously (Loske et al., 2000). Purity of the peptide was judged by
analytical HPLC to be >98%; the correct molecular weight was confirmed by mass spectrometry
(MALDI-TOF).
Culture medium supplemented with streptomycin=penicillin (100 mg=ml; 100U=ml) and 2mM L-glutamine.

The cell suspension volume plated was not informed in the paper.

Differentiation_protocol:
SH-SY5Y cells were maintained
in high glucose modified Eagle’s medium (DMEM) supplemented
with 10% fetal bovine serum and penicillin
(100U/ml)/streptomycin (100 μg/ml) at 37°C with 5%
CO2. The medium was refreshed every two days. Before
experiments, SH-SY5Y cells were seeded in DMEM with
1% fetal bovine serum for 24 h.
OBS:
The number of plated cells is not informed in the paper. Penicillin
(100U/ml)/streptomycin (100 μg/ml) was also added to the culture medium to maintain cell culture.

Medium was changed every three days and cells were passed once they reached approximately 80% confluence. The volume of cell suspension plated for the experiment is not informed in the paper. 50 ug/ml penicillin-streptomycin and OPI (150 ug/ml oxaloacetate, 50 ug/ml pyruvate and 0.2 U/ml insulin) were also added to the culture medium to maintain cell culture. The cells were allowed to attach and grow for two days prior to the treatment with Abeta peptide.

Differentiation_supplements: 1% penicillin–streptomycin, 10 μM all-trans retinoic acid, 50 ng/ml brain-derived neurotrophic factor
Differentiation_protocol:
SH-SY5Y (ATCC, Manassas, VA; CRL-2266) was maintained
in a 1:1 Dulbecco’s Modified Eagle’s Medium
(Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA)/Ham’s F-12 nutrient mixture
(Biosource, Camarillo, CA) supplemented with 10 % fetal
bovine serum (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) and 1 % penicillin–
streptomycin (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) (DF medium)
at 37°C in a humidified chamber with 5 % CO2. For neuronal
differentiation, a modification of the method of Encinas
et al. (2000) showed that a 3d BDNF exposure produced~
90 % of cells arrested in G1-phase. Cells (10,000 cm2) were
first plated in DF medium plus 10 μM all-trans retinoic acid
(RA; Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO) and cultured for 3 days.
Then the medium was changed to serum-free DF medium
plus 50 ng/ml brain-derived neurotrophic factor (BDNF; Chemicon, Temecula, CA), and cells were incubated for another 4 days.
OBS: Cell origin: ATCC, Manassas, VA; CRL-2266)

Medium_supplements: 2 mM L-glutamine; 1% of antibiotics including penicillin and streptomycin
Differentiation_protocol:
Cell cultures with
three to four passages were used for the experiments in compliance with
ATCC recommendation. After reaching 70−80% confluence, cells were
subcultured on poly(D-lysine) plates with 10 μM retinoic acid in a
reduced serum media (1% FBS) to induce postmitotic differentiation.27
Differentiation was confirmed by the change to polygonal morphology
and extension of long neurites.

SH-SY5Y human
neuroblastoma cells were seeded at a density of 3 × 105 cells/mL in a
6-well or 96-well poly(D-lysine) plate or a 10 cm poly(D-lysine) culture
dish in DMEM/F12 media containing 10 μMretinoic acid and 1% FBS
to induce postmitotic differentiation. The cells were incubated under
regular culture conditions for attachment. After 24 h of plating, the cells
were pretreated with different concentrations of test chemicals or a
vehicle control for 1 h following co-incubation with 5 or 10 μM Aβ42
during a desired time period.
OBS: The SH-SY5Y human neuroblastoma cell line was obtained from ATCC CRL-2266; Sigma-Aldrich, Saint Louis, MO. The results were normalized as the percentage of the neuroprotective activity relative to the Aβ42 free control (100%) and the 10 μMAβ42 treatment (0%). Cell cultures with three to four passages were used for the experiments in compliance with ATCC recommendation. The volume of cell suspension plated in 96 well plates is not informed.
